# Phase 212.H.2 — NuttX apps/external/<bringup>/Kconfig template.
#
# Surfaced under `Application Configuration → External Modules →
# nano-ros bringup` once symlinked into apps/external/<bringup>/. The
# sibling Make.defs gates `CONFIGURED_APPS` registration on this knob.
#
# The knob NAME is intentionally fixed (`NROS_BRINGUP_DEMO`) because
# NuttX's `apps/external/Kconfig` aggregator can't pass per-dir
# variables. A second bringup template gets staged at a sibling
# directory with its own (sed-rewritten) Kconfig copy.

config NROS_BRINGUP_DEMO
    bool "nano-ros multi-component bringup (demo)"
    default n
    depends on NROS
    help
      Enables a nano-ros multi-component bringup package staged at
      apps/external/<bringup>/. The Makefile's `context::` rule runs
      `nros codegen-system` to bake system.toml + launch/*.xml into
      compile-time C config, then cross-builds the bringup Rust
      workspace for the configured NuttX target triple.

      See docs/design/multi-node-workspace-layout.md for the
      `<bringup>` package shape (system.toml, launch/system.launch.xml,
      sibling component crates, optional nuttx_app_glue/).
